b'' b'' b'' b'************************************************************' b'* b'* attention all four wheel off road enthusiasts b'* b'* on/off road rally sunday, april 25th b'* joliet illinois b'* b'************************************************************' b'' b'the event:' b'' b'* the joliet mud turtles, a chicago land four wheel drive club, is' b'sponsoring an on/off road rally sunday april 25th.' b'' b'* for those who ask "what is an on/off road rally?", well...' b'' b'an on/off road rally consists of the following:' b'' b'1. an on-the-road rally where participants are given a set of' b'directions and clues guiding participates around the' b'joliet/plainfield area. the object is to navigate a course' b'based on a set of directions and clues. participants will' b'be given a set of questions pertaining to the course which' b'they must answer along the way. points are awarded for the' b'number of correct answers given. directions will ultimately' b'lead to an off-road area where a four-wheel drive course is' b'set-up. at various locations in the on-road course, check-points' b'will be set-up where participants will be asked other questions' b'or requested to perform some activity (e.g. tire roll, truck tow,' b'basketball free-throw, etc.) for additional points.' b'' b'2. an optional off-road, four wheel drive course where participants' b'will navigate off-road trails, mud bogs and/or hill climbs.' b'points are awarded for successfully navigating off-road obstacles' b'without getting stuck. if you should get stuck (which is half' b'the fun anyway), there will be assistance to get your vehicle' b'unstuck so you can try it again. the off-road course will' b'divided up based on tire size, so stock 4x4s as well as modified' b'4x4s can run the course.' b'' b'at the end of the rally, trophies will be awarded to top scoring' b'participants. door prizes and dash plaques will also be given out.' b'food and drinks also available at the conclusion.' b'' b'* this is an organized activity sponsored by the joliet mud turtles' b'so safety and fun is our foremost concern. all 4x4s must be' b'street legal and have solid tow points for the off-road section' b"of the course we don't want to have to separate someone's bumper" b'from their vehicle b'' b'the particulars:' b'' b'* rally begins at instant replay, plainfield road, joliet il.' b'(815)436-9382 (see map below)' b'* registration is between and a.m. first truck out at a.m.' b'* rally date is sunday april 25th, rain or shine' b'* there is an entry fee of per truck.' b'* you must have a co-driver (passengers allowed)' b'* a valid drivers license is required' b'* suggested equipment:' b'cb radio' b'compass' b'tow strap and clevis' b'clip board and pencil' b'* no alcohol during rally' b'* for more information contact' b'gary b'tom b'norm jr. b'brian b'' b'' b'__' b'instant b'| replay b'| 1.9mi mi north' b'|<-----| b'rt30 b'------|---------------------------------------------' b'exit b'257 b'| b'|rt55 |canton |larkin b'| |farm |ave b'| |rd. mi.' b'| b'| b'| b'| b'| rt80 v' b'----------------------------------------------------' b'| exit' b'| 130b' b'| b'' 